# API TOOLLAB

To start the toollab API in a dev environment, first copy .env-example to .env

```
cp .env.example .env
```

Change information on .env with yours

```
CURRENT_USER=githubdev
CURRENT_UID=1002
CURRENT_GID=1002
```

To find your username run this command line

```
whoami
```

To find your UID run this command line

```
id -u
```

To find your GID run this command line

```
id -g
```

And run

```
docker compose up -d
```

Command to be made in the project folder.

And that's it.

Projet run at http://localhost:8000/

## Réinitialiser la base avec les données de test
```
docker exec api_dev_toollab php artisan migrate:fresh --seed --force
```



### Réinitialiser sans seed

```
docker exec api_dev_toollab php artisan migrate:fresh --force && \
docker exec api_dev_toollab php artisan db:seed --class=ProductionSeeder --force && \
docker exec api_dev_toollab php artisan toollab:create-super-admin --password=password
```
